                    <h3 class="mod" data-uuid="8eb8e934affd4d69adffe4f6ddd787ef">Slavery in the United States, 1619–1852</h3>
                    <p class="mod" data-uuid="0cf5f853bda844039cbd7fb8a5261531">A growing abolitionist movement, fear of slave
                        rebellions, and industrialization in the textile industry shaped the
                        development of slavery in the United States. Slavery in the South continued
                        even after European nations had banned the slave trade and the United States had
                        made it illegal to import slaves.<br />
                    </p>
